<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1095344>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Map of southern Mendoza, eastern Neuquén, northwestern Río Negro and southwestern La Pampa provinces showing the complex landscape of this region with main orographic landmarks marked. White circles are main towns in the area, marked as reference, red lines are principal roads. Blue lines are main rivers, Colorado and Neuquén. Main mountain ranges, are marked.Inset:Regionin SouthAmérica.Line-dotted line show the political boundaries between four provinces cited above; other limits follow rivers and are not marked for simplicity. Localities sampled are shown with black (L. donosobarrosi, T.L.), red (L. donosobarrosi sp. 1), blue (L. donosobarrosi sp. 2) and green (L. donosobarrosi sp. 3) circles. Orange dotted line marks the approximate boundaries between the Patagonian Steppe and Southern Patagonian Monte." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1095344/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1095360>
    dc:description "FIGURE9. Type locality of Liolaemustirantii sp. nov. Upper:generalview of the area.Below:close view of the microhabitat where lizards were collected." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1095360/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

